<table align="center" cellpadding="10"><tr><td><img src="../images/foto_01.jpg" width="450" /></td><td>Mongolia (Монгол Улс) is a vast country located between the regions of Eastern and Central Asia. A landlocked nation, it borders Russia to the north and China to the south. A third of its population lives in the capital, Ulán Bator (Улаанбаатар). The total population does not reach three million inhabitants, which means that it's the least densely populated nation in the world. The mother tongue is Mongol, but Russian is also written and spoken, an inheritance from the soviet years. The changing Mongolian geography is just as remarkable and attractive: flat steppes, mountains and deserts are scattered throughout its over one and a half million square kilometers. The largest amount of nature reserves of the world is concentrated in its huge territory: 20 million hectares have been declared protected areas, the equivalent of 14% of its total surface.<div align="right"><p>
